{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"6e480942-4fdd-4f0a-a648-fda846564a83","content":"Here are the pod spec changes for automatic crash dump collection:\n\n```yaml\nspec:\n  # Required for createdump to ptrace the crashing process\n  shareProcessNamespace: true\n  containers:\n  - name: myapp\n    env:\n    - name: DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump\n      value: \"1\"\n    - name: DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpType\n      value: \"4\"                          # Full dump (1=Normal, 2=WithPrivateRW, 3=Triage, 4=Full)\n    - name: DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpName\n      value: \"/tmp/dumps/coredump.%p.%t\"  # %p=PID, %t=timestamp\n    - name: DOTNET_DbgCreatedumpPath\n      value: \"/opt/tools/createdump\"\n    securityContext:\n      capabilities:\n        add:\n        - SYS_PTRACE                      # Required by createdump\n    volumeMounts:\n    - name: crash-dumps\n      mountPath: /tmp/dumps\n  volumes:\n  - name: crash-dumps\n    emptyDir:\n      sizeLimit: 2Gi                      # Adjust to your app's memory footprint\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n\n- **`SYS_PTRACE`** — `createdump` uses `ptrace` to snapshot the process; this capability is mandatory.\n- **`DOTNET_DbgCreatedumpPath`** — tells the NativeAOT runtime where `createdump` lives (it's not bundled like with CoreCLR).\n- **`MiniDumpType 4`** — gives a full heap dump for best debuggability; use `1` (Normal) for smaller files.\n- **`emptyDir`** — dumps survive container restarts within the pod's lifetime. Swap for a PVC or sidecar upload if you need persistence beyond pod eviction.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"76364edb-dbdf-43ac-b4b2-a80f50f22d5b","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to configure automatic crash dump collection for a NativeAOT .NET 11 app running in Kubernetes. They have `createdump` installed at `/opt/tools/createdump`. Let me provide the necessary environment variables and pod spec changes.\n\nFor .NET crash dump collection, the key environment variables are:\n- `DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump=1` — enables automatic crash dump generation\n- `DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpType=4` — full dump (MiniDumpWithFullMemory). Types: 1=Normal, 2=WithPrivateReadWriteMemory, 3=FilterTriage, 4=Full\n\n\n- `DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpName` — path/pattern for the dump file\n- `DOTNET_CreateDumpDiagnostics=1` — optional, enables diagnostics for createdump itself\n\nFor NativeAOT specifically, since .NET 8+, NativeAOT supports crash dumps via createdump using these same environment variables. I'm working through the environment variables for dump configuration — `DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump=1` enables it, `DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpType` controls the dump type, and `DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpName` sets the output path with placeholders for process ID and timestamp. For NativeAOT specifically, the createdump tool path handling is different since it's not bundled with the runtime like it is for CoreCLR. Configuring the pod spec with the necessary environment variables and volume mounts...","outputTokens":1737,"requestId":"1BC1:2AB0E:15A6883:1856983:6A028691"},"id":"b19f1c7a-b824-4732-9226-9d75f0b4275b","timestamp":"2026-05-12T01:47:30.695Z","parentId":"b74acc23-5feb-4cd9-854d-fb7ee7cfb63d"}
